ousUserHome);\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void createsConfiguredFailureDetailViewByClassName() throws IOException {\\n        ExposedTestRunner runner = runnerWithPreferences(\\n                \\\"FailureViewClass=\\\" + RecordingFailureDetailView.class.getName());\\n\\n        FailureDetailView view = runner.newFailureDetailView();\\n\\n        assertThat(view).isInstanceOf(RecordingFailureDetailView.class);\\n        assertThat(view.getComponent()).isInstanceOf(JLabel.class);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void createsConfiguredTestCollectorByClassNameWhenBrowsing() throws IOException {\\n        EmptyTestCollector.createdInstances = 0;\\n        ExposedTestRunner runner = runnerWithPreferences(\\\"TestCollectorClass=\\\" + EmptyTestCollector.class.getName());\\n\\n        Throwable thrown = catchThrowable(runner::browseTestClasses);\\n\\n        assertThat(EmptyTestCollector.createdInstances).isEqualTo(1);\\n        assertThat(thrown).isInstanceOfAny(HeadlessException.class, NullPointerException.class);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void createsLogoFromRunnerResource() throws IOException {\\n        ExposedTestRunner runner = runnerWithPreferences();\\n\\n        JLabel logo = runner.newLogo();\\n        Icon icon = TestRunner.getIconResource(BaseTestRunner.class, \\\"logo.gif\\\");\\n\\n        assertThat(logo.getIcon()).isNotNull();\\n        assertThat(icon).isNotNull();\\n        assertThat(logo.getToolTipText()).startsWith(\\\"JUnit Version \\\");\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void rerunReloadsTestCaseThroughStringConstructor() throws Throwable {\\n        ExposedTestRunner runner = runnerWithPreferences();\\n        runner.setLoading(false);\\n        ReloadableTestCase.constructedNames.clear();\\n        ReloadableTestCase original = new ReloadableTestCase(\\\"testNeverRuns\\\");\\n\\n        Method rerunTest = TestRunner.class.getDeclaredMethod(\\\"rerunTest\\\", junit.framework.Test.class);\\n        rerunTest.setAccessible(true);\\n        Throwable thrown = catchThrowable(() -> rerunTest.invoke(runner, original));\\n\\n        assertThat(thrown).isInstanceOf(InvocationTargetException.class);\\n        assertThat(((InvocationTargetException) thrown).getCause()).isInstanceOf(NullPointerException.class);\\n        assertThat(ReloadableTestCase.constructedNames).containsExactly(\\\"testNeverRuns\\\", \\\"testNeverRuns\\\");\\n    }\\n\\n    private ExposedTestRunner runnerWithPreferences(String... lines) throws IOException {\\n        previousUserHome = System.getProperty(\\\"user.home\\\");\\n        System.setProperty(\\\"user.home\\\", temporaryHome.toString());\\n        if (lines.length > 0) {\\n            Files.writeString(temporaryHome.resolve(\\\"junit.properties\\\"), String.join(System.lineSeparator(), lines));\\n        }\\n        return new ExposedTestRunner();\\n    }\\n\\n    public static class RecordingFailureDetailView implements FailureDetailView {\\n        private final JLabel component = new JLabel(\\\"failure details\\\");\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public void clear() {\\n            component.setText(\\\"\\\");\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public Component getComponent() {\\n            return component;\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public void showFailure(TestFailure failure) {\\n            component.setText(failure.toString());\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    public static class EmptyTestCollector implements TestCollector {\\n        static int createdInstances;\\n\\n        public EmptyTestCollector() {\\n            createdInstances++;\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public Enumeration collectTests() {\\n            return Collections.enumeration(Collections.emptyList());\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    public static class ReloadableTestCase extends TestCase {\\n        static final List<String> constructedNames = new ArrayList<>();\\n\\n        public ReloadableTestCase(String name) {\\n            super(name);\\n            constructedNames.add(name);\\n        }\\n\\n        public void testNeverRuns() {\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static class ExposedTestRunner extends TestRunner {\\n        FailureDetailView newFailureDetailView() {\\n            return createFailureDetailView();\\n        }\\n\\n        JLabel newLogo() {\\n            return createLogo();\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777934661066}}\n[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Exploring dialog interactions**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how to dispose of any dialog with the title \\\"About.\\\" If I don't find it right away, I might need to repeat until it appears. I wonder if using a latch could help here? Also, I need to remember that timer events fire on EDT. If `doClick` is on the test thread, can the EDT handle it? I think calling `item.doClick(0)` on the test thread triggers the action synchronously rather than on the EDT.\\n\\n**Considering exception handling**\\n\\nI could consider using `CountDownLatch` with `finished.countDown()` in the `finally` block. I'll wait for 5 seconds, but there's a potential issue: if no display is available or a `HeadlessException` is thrown in the Event Dispatch Thread (EDT), the latch counts down without showing a dialog, which may cause the test to fail based on existing assumptions about the display. I also need to capture exceptions with `AtomicReference<Throwable>`, but exceptions in `invokeLater` wonât propagate, so I should catch `Throwable`.\\n\\n**Inspecting test utilities**\\n\\nI'm considering whether I need fully qualified imports. The AGENTS seems to suggest importing classes, so thatâs something to explore. I think it might help to inspect the existing TestRunnerTest for possible insights into utility styles. It's a bit of a puzzle, but I'm looking forward to putting the pieces together and figuring out the best approach!\", \"thinkingSigna