kbD4awiKXt50pgWRWlpBB1wgyfFFM78wwgWsN-RHo2mUNTt13o6Ja2nkDihIDa8pWmd1w7vhoVduBlmcRNBkWAcjzkeSDKCG8nARcejkKrN6wnXbpLe-pIftBXTyOpVODX0r1ApcItpnvOI5J7bg2L7uo5XyorQkGU7fmzYywLD7HRnvX2vntn-gDM2PZRqB-VDV4siqO5UCJWEJXplSDNvpScyecXDLnMf3JEDHhL5HUq24XjI1xI7krw4e7upScjg4eRTKhIVlQ\\\",\\\"summary\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Exploring dialog interactions**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about how to dispose of any dialog with the title \\\\\\\"About.\\\\\\\" If I don't find it right away, I might need to repeat until it appears. I wonder if using a latch could help here? Also, I need to remember that timer events fire on EDT. If `doClick` is on the test thread, can the EDT handle it? I think calling `item.doClick(0)` on the test thread triggers the action synchronously rather than on the EDT.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering exception handling**\\\\n\\\\nI could consider using `CountDownLatch` with `finished.countDown()` in the `finally` block. I'll wait for 5 seconds, but there's a potential issue: if no display is available or a `HeadlessException` is thrown in the Event Dispatch Thread (EDT), the latch counts down without showing a dialog, which may cause the test to fail based on existing assumptions about the display. I also need to capture exceptions with `AtomicReference<Throwable>`, but exceptions in `invokeLater` wonât propagate, so I should catch `Throwable`.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Inspecting test utilities**\\\\n\\\\nI'm considering whether I need fully qualified imports. The AGENTS seems to suggest importing classes, so thatâs something to explore. I think it might help to inspect the existing TestRunnerTest for possible insights into utility styles. It's a bit of a puzzle, but I'm looking forward to putting the pieces together and figuring out the best approach!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_tA4HL4hh76zXpo6MNtItiAj2|fc_0d78c524247685cf0169f921446d