modal dialog execution**\\\\n\\\\nIâm considering running an action directly in a daemon executor without using invokeLater. Modal dialogs are generally meant to be on the EDT, but they can be shown off it, especially in tests. I think using a background thread for doClick might help avoid reentrant issues with invokeAndWait. However, I have to consider how modal dialogs function on the EDT, since they create a nested event pump. I also need to check for any deprecated issues with dialog.show.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Addressing test coverage issues**\\\\n\\\\nI'm concerned about a potential issue where final assert clickFailure might return null after the \\\\\\\"HeadlessException\\\\\\\" is set. If thereâs no display, the test could fail after waiting 5 seconds, but that's not a pressing issue. Iâm thinking about whether to use AtomicReference<Throwable>, since checkstyle forbids using \\\\\\\"Throwable.\\\\\\\" There's an existing catchThrowable, and I might not even need to run tests if the compile isnât necessary. But, the user did request to improve test coverage, so Iâll have to consider that.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Added `tests/src/junit/junit/3.7/src/test/java/junit_junit/AboutDialogTest.java`.\\n\\nThe new dedicated test exercises `junit.swingui.AboutDialog` through the public Swing UI menu path (`TestRunner#createJUnitMenu()`), opens the About dialog, verifies it appears, and disposes it with bounded waits so the modal dialog cannot hang indefinitely.\\n\\nI did not run compilation or tests, per instruction.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0d78c524247685cf0169f9216808b0819f98930697059a0616\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 439, \"output\": 583, \"cacheRead\": 52224, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 53246, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRea